# Implementation Plan: Cinematic Obsidian Overhaul

## Goal
Transform GoLive into a cinematic, high-end platform that feels distinct from Twitch. We are moving towards **"Obsidian Minimalism"** (Apple's precision + Netflix's immersive dark mode).

## Proposed Changes

### [Design System]
- **Theme Shift**: Replace Twitch Purple (`#9147ff`) with **Electric Crimson** (`#E50914`) for accents, and use a deep Obsidian base (`#050505`).
- **Precision Borders**: Use `1px` solid borders with `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1)` and subtle inner shadows.
- **Glass Refinement**: Use a more subtle "Frosted Glass" (20% opacity) for headers and sidebars.

### [Components Overhaul]
#### [MODIFY] [globals.css](file:///C:/GOLive/app/globals.css)
- Update `@theme` block with new primary colors and radius variables (shifting to sharper `6px` / `8px` corners for the Netflix look).
- Redesign `auth-card` and `auth-input` classes.

#### [MODIFY] [Navbar.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/Navbar.tsx)
- Redesign the **Search Box**: Centered, minimal, pill-shaped with a glowing border on focus.
- Update **Login/Signup** buttons to be clear Apple-style "outlined" and "filled" crimson.

#### [MODIFY] [HomeClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/HomeClient.tsx)
- Replace grid layout with a more cinematic "featured row" at the top.
- Ensure all category chips match the new crimson/black theme.

#### [MODIFY] [VideoCard.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx)
- Add "Verified" badge logic.
- Implement Apple-style scale and border transition on hover.

### [Auth Pages]
#### [MODIFY] [login/page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/login/page.tsx) & [register/page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/register/page.tsx)
- Strip all "messy" elements.
- Use a pure centered card with elegant, wide-spaced inputs and no distracting background glows.

## Data & Database
- **Schema**: Add `is_verified` column to `profiles` if missing.
- **Production cleanup**: Sweep components for `pravatar.cc` or `unsplash.com` links and replace with empty states or `DiceBear` user-tied seeds.

## Verification
- **Simulated Agents**: I will run a 20-agent simulation to check for edge cases.
- **Build**: Final production build verification before push.
